The hard way-
we create a whole new inverted tree.
if root is null: return root
create a newroot = new TreeNode(root->val)
create two queue: oldq,newq;
push newroot,root
while(queues are not empty):
  take the front of the both queues
  pop them
  if(root left):
    create a newNode= new TreeNode(root->left)
    then connect it with the newroot's right
    push root's left and newroot's right to their respective queue
  if(root right):
    create a newNode=new TreeNode(root->right)
    then connect it with the newroot's left
    push root's right and newroot's left to their respective queue
return newroot
